<P>
   EURO-TOURISM (Undated) _ When Mark Lesser got married in 1985,
he priced a honeymoon in Paris. Even though the dollar was then
stronger than at any time since the early 1970s, the trip was out
of the question. But in August, Lesser, 37, will celebrate his 15th
anniversary with his wife, Stacy, in Paris and Nice. Like other
American travelers, the Lessers are reveling not only in their
increased income, but also in their incredible buying power abroad.
The value of the dollar has surged recently against most of the
world's currencies, especially against the euro. By Jonathan
Fuerbringer.
