<SLUG> BC-CAMPAIGN-SCOTUS-REVIEW-2NDTAKE-NYT </SLUG>
  
 WASHINGTON: anti-abortion position.  
<TEXT>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Unlike Bush, Gore has not been timid about saying he would pick
justices who share his view on abortion, which is pro-choice.
</P>
<P>
   Even President Clinton weighed in the other day. ``If they get
two to four appointments on the Supreme Court,'' he said, ``I think
Roe vs. Wade will be repealed and a lot of other things that have
been a part of the fabric of our constitutional life will be
