<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-LADN-BUDGET </SLUG>
  
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following general
stories for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs on
Sunday, May 21, and thereafter. For questions about stories,
contact Gerry Hoppe at the Daily News, (818) 713-3702.
</P>
<P>
   PARKS-INTERVIEW (Los Angeles) _ In an exclusive interview, Chief
Bernard C. Parks defends the LAPD against federal ``pattern'' of
civil rights violations allegations. The ACLU says he's wrong. By
Beth Barrett. (Will move in the ``a'' national news file and in the
``n'' California news file.)
</P>
<P>
   HOMES-FICKETT (Los Angeles) _ It could be called the ``San
Fernando Valley'' school of architecture: the thousands of
low-slung homes that Edward Fickett designed with large glass
windows, partial windows and, best of all, low cost. Fickett, who
died recently, pioneered many designs that are now signature for
low-cost developments nationwide. His widow is cataloging Pickett
homes in the Valley to preserve his legacy. By Steve Carney. (Will
move in the ``a'' national and ``n'' California news files.)
</P>
