<P>
   NY-REPUBS-SENATE (New York) _ Rep. Rick Lazio of Long Island
came roaring into the race for senator from New York Saturday,
attacking Hillary Rodham Clinton as a ``far-left, extremist''
candidate who has ``no real rationale for serving here other than
as a steppingstone to some other position.'' By Adam Nagourney.
</P>
<P>
   (We plan to move the story by 2 p.m. ET in ``p'' news file.)
</P>
<P>
   Top center story:
</P>
<P>
   CHINA-TRADE (Beijing) _ The Clinton administration has argued
that Congress should vote for normal trade relations with China
because it will strengthen reformist forces in China. The vast
majority of influential Chinese agree. For millions of Chinese, in
fact, the congressional vote _ which, if positive, would ensure
China's full participation in the World Trade Organization _ has
taken on a transcendent aura beyond the boundaries of trade or
politics. By Elisabeth Rosenthal with Joseph Kahn.
</P>
<P>
   (Scheduled to move by 2 p.m. ET in ``i'' news file.)
