presidential candidate seem to go back to his childhood in Midland,
a conservative, up-from-the-bootstraps town that has grown from
25,000 when he was a little boy to almost 100,000 today. A special
report. Articles in this series will examine the lives of the
presidential candidates as the campaign progresses. By Nicholas D.
