   BOTTOM
</P>
<P>
   MEDICINE-MERCHANTS (Omugo, Uganda) _ Melarsoprol is melarsen
oxide dissolved in propylene glycol _ literally, arsenic in
antifreeze. It kills 5 percent of those treated with it. But it is
the only medicine available to treat advanced sleeping sickness,
one of the historic scourges of Africa. The only alternative ran
out in July after the manufacturer abandoned it as unprofitable
when it turned out to be useless against its intended target,
cancer. Sleeping sickness is perhaps the most vivid example of the
disconnection between the world's pharmaceutical giants and the
fatal or debilitating diseases of the Third World's poor. A special
report. By Donald G. McNeil Jr.
</P>
<P>
   With map.
</P>
