<P>
   COXNET FOCUS 0520: BACK IN THE '50s -- The Perseghettis have all
the trappings of a busy family in the year 2000. Their
three-bedroom ranch in this suburb south of Dayton bristles with
technology including four computers, four phones and an answering
machine. But what if, for one week, all the amenities of the last
half-century disappeared? No word processing, e-mailing or cordless
telephones. No dishwasher, clothes dryer or microwave. That's what
we wanted to find out when we went looking for a family who would
forgo all modern conveniences _ essentially live in a 1950s bubble
_ for seven days. (DeBrosse, Dayton Daily News)
</P>
