there among the warriors in the closing days of the Persian Gulf
war, rather than having to marshal their recollections nearly a
decade later, he would have been able to write an unquestionably
definitive account. Had more reporters been on the scene, it's
quite possible that some events might have unfolded differently.
(Andy Glass is a columnist for Cox News Service in the Washington
bureau.) MOVED THURSDAY.
