<P>
   SKIP-CARAY _ Skip Caray is entering his 25th year as TV and
radio broadcaster of the Atlanta Braves. Part of a blue-blooded
announcing lineage _ father Harry is in the baseball hall of fame,
son Chip is current announcer of the Cubs _ Skip is like neither of
them. Weaned on announcing baseball back in the bad old Braves
days, he's known to be more sarcastic than sentimental. He says
this year he's the ``new'' Skip _ he's quit drinking, lost weight,
and promises not to bite the heads off callers who phone his
pregame show and ask, for the umpteenth time, how to compute a
slugging percentage. We'll see. (Jubera, Cox News Service). 88.
WITH PHOTOS and LAYOUT. MOVED
