<HEADLINE>
 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
   
 c. 1999 The Kansas City Star  
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Kansas City Star will publish a two-part series, with
sidebars and graphics, on Sunday and Monday, May 21 and 22, about
police nationwide circumventing state laws in order to keep drug
money they seize. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   The stories, with a home slug of DRUG-MONEY, are available for
use by clients of The New York Times News Service. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Please note that while the stories are long, they are rich in
detail from cases around the country. For this reason, the stories
will have trim indicators, enabling clients to excise material of
less interest to readers in their region. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   In addition, The Star is offering a shorter version of the
DRUG-MONEY-I story, slugged DRUG-MONEY-SHORT. &QL;
