   DRUG-MONEY-I Kansas City -- Local and state police nationwide
work with federal agencies to keep drug money they seize even
though many state laws clearly intend the money to go education or
other public funds. In fact, little-known provisions in most state
laws would block the way the police//federal partnership now works.
The police practice leads to aggressive searches and a loss of
civil liberties, critics say. By Karen Dillon. 3400 words. &QL;
</P>
