</P>
<P>
   THE WINSTON FIELD OF 20 BOX
</P>
<P>
   PETTY COLUMN _ Lee Petty was the past, the foundation of
stock-car racing's model family. Adam Petty was the future, a loss
not just to racing alone, but to man in general, for he was as
straight-laced as they come, clear-eyed, clear-headed. Born to be
the next ``King,'' succeeding to the title held by the grandfather
Richard. (Bisher, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   MAKING HEADLINES _ Lowe's Motor Speedway President Humpy Wheeler
has predicted the winner of The Winston eight times in the last 12
years. (Carvell, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
