<P>
   (NYT13) BEIJING -- May 20, 2000 -- CHINA-TRADE-COX-1 -- The way
Chinese factory workers see it, lay-offs loom inevitably in their
future, regardless of any vote by the U.S. Congress or whether
China joins any world trade bodies. The state-run factories they
work at are dinosaurs left-over from the era of the planned economy
and will most likely not make it in the era of global economic
competition. A worker at the Beijing Textile Machine Factory, where
equipment is outdated and layoffs are looming. (Julie Chao/Cox News
Service Photo)
</P>
<P>
